{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id43d2ea3e-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s545"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"545"},"text":"§ 545.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Undistributed personal holding company income","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id43d2ea3f-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s545/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Definition","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"For purposes of this part, the term “undistributed personal holding company income” means the taxable income of a personal holding company adjusted in the manner provided in subsections (b), (c), and (d), minus the dividends paid deduction as defined in section 561. In the case of a personal holding company which is a foreign corporation, not more than 10 percent in value of the outstanding stock of which is owned (within the meaning of section 958(a)) during the last half of the taxable year by United States persons, the term “undistributed personal holding company income” means the amount determined by multiplying the undistributed personal holding company income (determined without regard to this sentence) by the percentage in value of its outstanding stock which is the greatest percentage in value of its outstanding stock so owned by United States persons on any one day during such period.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id43d2ea40-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s545/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Adjustments to taxable income","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"For the purposes of subsection (a), the taxable income shall be adjusted as follows:","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id43d2ea41-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s545/b/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Taxes","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"There shall be allowed as a deduction Federal income and excess profits taxes and income, war profits and excess profits taxes of foreign countries and possessions of the United States (to the extent not allowable as a deduction under section 275(a)(4)), accrued during the taxable year or deemed to be paid by a domestic corporation under section 960 for the taxable year, but not including the accumulated earnings tax imposed by section 531 or the personal holding company tax imposed by section 541.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id43d2ea42-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s545/b/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Charitable contributions","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The deduction for charitable contributions provided under section 170 shall be allowed, but in computing such deduction the limitations in section 170(b)(1)(A), (B), (D), and (E) shall apply, and section 170(b)(2) and (d)(1) shall not apply. For purposes of this paragraph, the term “contribution base” when used in section 170(b)(1) means the taxable income computed with the adjustments (other than the 10-percent limitation) provided in section 170(b)(2) and (d)(1) and without deduction of the amount disallowed under paragraph (6) of this subsection.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id43d2ea43-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s545/b/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Special deductions disallowed","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The special deductions for corporations provided in part VIII (except section 248) of subchapter B (section 241 and following, relating to the deduction for dividends received by corporations, etc.) shall not be allowed.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id43d2ea44-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s545/b/4"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"4"},"text":"(4)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Net operating loss","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The net operating loss deduction provided in section 172 shall not be allowed, but there shall be allowed as a deduction the amount of the net operating loss (as defined in section 172(c)) for the preceding taxable year computed without the deductions provided in part VIII (except section 248) of subchapter B.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id43d2ea45-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s545/b/5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"5"},"text":"(5)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Net capital gains","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"There shall be allowed as a deduction the net capital gain for the taxable year, minus the taxes imposed by this subtitle attributable to such net capital gain. The taxes attributable to such net capital gain shall be an amount equal to the difference between—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id43d2ea46-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s545/b/5/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the taxes imposed by this subtitle (except the tax imposed by this part) for such year, and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id43d2ea47-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s545/b/5/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" such taxes computed for such year without including such excess in taxable income.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id43d2ea48-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s545/b/6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"6"},"text":"(6)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Expenses and depreciation applicable to property of the taxpayer","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"The aggregate of the deductions allowed under section 162 (relating to trade or business expenses) and section 167 (relating to depreciation), which are allocable to the operation and maintenance of property owned or operated by the corporation, shall be allowed only in an amount equal to the rent or other compensation received for the use of, or the right to use, the property, unless it is established (under regulations prescribed by the Secretary) to the satisfaction of the Secretary—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id43d2ea49-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s545/b/6/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" that the rent or other compensation received was the highest obtainable, or, if none was received, that none was obtainable;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id43d2ea4a-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s545/b/6/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" that the property was held in the course of a business carried on bona fide for profit; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id43d2ea4b-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s545/b/6/C"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"C"},"text":"(C)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" either that there was reasonable expectation that the operation of the property would result in a profit, or that the property was necessary to the conduct of the business.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id43d2ea4c-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s545/b/7"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"7"},"text":"(7)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Special rule for capital gains and losses of foreign corporations","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In the case of a foreign corporation, paragraph (5) shall be applied by taking into account only gains and losses which are effectively connected with the conduct of a trade or business within the United States and are not exempt from tax under treaty.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id43d2ea4d-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s545/c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"c"},"text":"(c)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Certain foreign corporations","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In the case of a foreign corporation all of the outstanding stock of which during the last half of the taxable year is owned by nonresident alien individuals (whether directly or indirectly through foreign estates, foreign trusts, foreign partnerships, or other foreign corporations), the taxable income for purposes of subsection (a) shall be the income which constitutes personal holding company income under section 543(a)(7), reduced by the deductions attributable to such income, and adjusted, with respect to such income, in the manner provided in subsection (b).","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id43d2ea4e-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1954-08-16/ch736"},"text":"Aug. 16, 1954, ch. 736","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/68A/189"},"text":"68A Stat. 189","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/85/866/tI/s32/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 85–866, title I, § 32(a)","children":[],"tail":", (b), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1958-09-02"},"text":"Sept. 2, 1958","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/72/1631"},"text":"72 Stat. 1631","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/87/403/s3/d"},"text":"Pub. L. 87–403, § 3(d)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1962-02-02"},"text":"Feb. 2, 1962","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/76/7"},"text":"76 Stat. 7","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/87/834/s9/d/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 87–834, § 9(d)(2)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1962-10-16"},"text":"Oct. 16, 1962","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/76/1001"},"text":"76 Stat. 1001","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/88/272/tII"},"text":"Pub. L. 88–272, title II","children":[],"tail":", §§ 207(b)(5), 209(c)(2), 225(i)(1), (2), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1964-02-26"},"text":"Feb. 26, 1964","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/78/42"},"text":"78 Stat. 42","children":[],"tail":", 46, 90; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/89/719/tI/s101/b/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 89–719, title I, § 101(b)(2)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1966-11-02"},"text":"Nov. 2, 1966","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/80/1132"},"text":"80 Stat. 1132","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/89/809/tI/s104/h/3"},"text":"Pub. L. 89–809, title I, § 104(h)(3)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1966-11-13"},"text":"Nov. 13, 1966","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/80/1560"},"text":"80 Stat. 1560","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/91/172/tII/s201/a/2/B"},"text":"Pub. L. 91–172, title II, § 201(a)(2)(B)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1969-12-30"},"text":"Dec. 30, 1969","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/83/558"},"text":"83 Stat. 558","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/94/455/tX/s1033/b/4"},"text":"Pub. L. 94–455, title X, § 1033(b)(4)","children":[],"tail":", title XIX, §§ 1901(a)(77), (b)(20)(B), (32)(E), (33)(D), 1906(b)(13)(A), 1951(b)(9)(A), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1976-10-04"},"text":"Oct. 4, 1976","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/90/1628"},"text":"90 Stat. 1628","children":[],"tail":", 1777, 1797, 1800, 1801, 1834, 1839; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/448/tI/s102/m/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–448, title I, § 102(m)(2)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1983-01-12"},"text":"Jan. 12, 1983","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/96/2374"},"text":"96 Stat. 2374","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/514/tXII/s1225/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 99–514, title XII, § 1225(b)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1986-10-22"},"text":"Oct. 22, 1986","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/100/2559"},"text":"100 Stat. 2559","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/508/tXI/s11801/a/24"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–508, title XI, § 11801(a)(24)","children":[],"tail":", (c)(10)(B), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1990-11-05"},"text":"Nov. 5, 1990","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/104/1388-521"},"text":"104 Stat. 1388–521","children":[],"tail":", 1388–527; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/109/280/tXII/s1206/b/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 109–280, title XII, § 1206(b)(2)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2006-08-17"},"text":"Aug. 17, 2006","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/120/1070"},"text":"120 Stat. 1070","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/113/295/dA/tII/s221/a/64"},"text":"Pub. L. 113–295, div. A, title II, § 221(a)(64)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2014-12-19"},"text":"Dec. 19, 2014","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/128/4048"},"text":"128 Stat. 4048","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/115/97/tI/s14301/c/4"},"text":"Pub. L. 115–97, title I, § 14301(c)(4)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2017-12-22"},"text":"Dec. 22, 2017","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/131/2222"},"text":"131 Stat. 2222","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id43d2ea4f-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id43d2ea50-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"id43d2ea51-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2017—Subsec. (b)(1). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/115/97"},"text":"Pub. L. 115–97","children":[],"tail":" substituted “section 960” for “section 902(a) or 960(a)(1)”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2014—Subsec. (b)(1). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/113/295"},"text":"Pub. L. 113–295","children":[],"tail":" substituted “section 531 or the personal holding company tax imposed by section 541.” for “section 531, the personal holding company tax imposed by section 541, or the taxes imposed by corresponding sections of a prior income tax law.”"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2006—Subsec. (b)(2). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/109/280"},"text":"Pub. L. 109–280","children":[],"tail":", which directed the substitution of “(D), and (E)” for “and (D)” in section 545(b)(2), without specifying the act to be amended, was executed by making the substitution in subsec. (b)(2) of this section, which is section 545 of the Internal Revenue Code of 1986, to reflect the probable intent of Congress."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1990—Subsecs. (c), (d). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/508"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–508","children":[],"tail":" redesignated subsec. (d) as (c) and struck out former subsec. (c) which related to a special adjustment to taxable income for amounts used or set aside to pay or retire qualified indebtedness."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1986—Subsec. (b)(7). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/514"},"text":"Pub. L. 99–514","children":[],"tail":" added par. (7)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1983—Subsec. (b)(2). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/448"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–448","children":[],"tail":" substituted “10-percent” for “5-percent”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1976—Subsec. (b)(1). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/94/455"},"text":"Pub. L. 94–455","children":[],"tail":", §§ 1033(b)(4), 1901(a)(77)(A), struck out “(other than excess profits tax imposed by subchapter E of chapter 2 of the Internal Revenue Code of 1939 for taxable years beginning after "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1940-12-31"},"text":"December 31, 1940","children":[],"tail":")” after “Federal income and excess profits taxes”; substituted “902(a) or 960(a)(1)” for “902(a)(1) or 960(a)(1)(C)” after “corporation under section”; and struck out provisions after “prior income tax law” relating to election by taxpayer who paid Federal income and excess profits taxes to deduct payments, when made, for purposes of computing subchapter A net income or, for a taxable year ending after "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1954-06-30"},"text":"June 30, 1954","children":[],"tail":", to deduct such taxes when accrued, such election being irrevocable and applied to taxable year for which election was made and to all subsequent taxable years."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (b)(2). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/94/455/s1901/b/20/B/ii"},"text":"Pub. L. 94–455, § 1901(b)(20)(B)(ii)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “paragraph (6)” for “paragraph (8)” after “amount disallowed under”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (b)(5). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/94/455/s1901/b/33/D"},"text":"Pub. L. 94–455, § 1901(b)(33)(D)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “Net” for “Long-term” after “(5)”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (b)(6). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/94/455"},"text":"Pub. L. 94–455","children":[],"tail":", §§ 1901(b)(20)(B)(i), 1906(b)(13)(A), struck out par. (6) relating to deduction allowed to bank affiliates, redesignated former par. (8) as (6) and, as redesignated, struck out “or his delegate” in two places after “Secretary”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (b)(7). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/94/455/s1901/a/77/B"},"text":"Pub. L. 94–455, § 1901(a)(77)(B)","children":[],"tail":", struck out par. (7) relating to payment of indebtedness incurred prior to "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1934-01-01"},"text":"January 1, 1934","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (b)(8). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/94/455/s1901/b/20/B/i"},"text":"Pub. L. 94–455, § 1901(b)(20)(B)(i)","children":[],"tail":", redesignated par. (8) as (6)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (b)(9). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/94/455/s1951/b/9/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 94–455, § 1951(b)(9)(A)","children":[],"tail":", struck out par. (9) relating to the deduction of the amount of a lien in favor of the United States."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (b)(10), (11). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/94/455/s1901/b/32/E"},"text":"Pub. L. 94–455, § 1901(b)(32)(E)","children":[],"tail":", struck out par. (10) relating to deduction for distributions of divested stock, and struck out par. (11) relating to special adjustment on the disposition of antitrust stock received as a dividend."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (c)(2)(A). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/94/455/s1901/a/77/C"},"text":"Pub. L. 94–455, § 1901(a)(77)(C)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “"},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1964-02-26"},"text":"February 26, 1964","children":[],"tail":"” for “the date of enactment of this subsection” after “years ending before”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (c)(4). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/94/455/s1906/b/13/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 94–455, § 1906(b)(13)(A)","children":[],"tail":", struck out “or his delegate” after “Secretary”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (c)(5). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/94/455/s1901/b/20/B/iii"},"text":"Pub. L. 94–455, § 1901(b)(20)(B)(iii)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “subsection (b)(6)” for “subsection (b)(8)” after “company income under”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1969—Subsec. (b)(2). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/91/172"},"text":"Pub. L. 91–172","children":[],"tail":" substituted “section 170(b)(1)(A), (B), and (D)”, “section 170(b)(2) and (d)(1)” for “section 170(b)(1)(A) and (B)” and “section 170(b)(2) and (5)”, respectively, in provisions of first sentence setting out the sections appropriate to the computation of the deduction, and in provisions of second sentence describing applicability of terms for purposes of this paragraph, substituted “contribution base” and “section 170(b)(2) and (d)(1)” for “adjusted gross income” and “the first sentence of section 170(b)(2) and (5),” respectively."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1966—Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/89/809/s104/h/3/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 89–809, § 104(h)(3)(A)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “in the manner provided in subsections (b), (c), and (d)” for “in the manner provided in subsection (b) and (c)” and inserted provisions governing the case of a personal holding company which is a foreign corporation, not more than 10 percent in value of the outstanding stock of which is owned (within the meaning of s